</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-28_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Blood loss from injuries or medical conditions requires immediate attention as it can lead to shock, organ failure, or even death if not managed promptly. According to Health and Safety Executive (HSE) guidelines, around 30% of preventable deaths in trauma situations are due to bleeding. Recognising the signs and knowing the correct first aid procedures can significantly increase survival rates.
