</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Direct pressure</strong> -The first and most effective step in controlling bleeding.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Tourniquet </strong>- A device that applies pressure to a limb or extremity to stop severe bleeding.




</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-41_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-42_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-43_ pf-heading-1-h3">Legislation and regulations</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-45_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In the UK, the Health and Safety (First-Aid) Regulations 1981 mandate that employers provide adequate and appropriate equipment, facilities, and personnel to ensure immediate and effective first aid in the event of an injury. This includes training employees in handling emergency situations involving significant blood loss.
