</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-54_ pf-text-1"><strong>Use of tourniquets </strong>- For severe limb bleeding where direct pressure is insufficient, the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) recommends using tourniquets as an effective life-saving technique.





</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-56_ pf-text-1"><strong>Positioning </strong>- Keeping the victim calm and lying down, elevate the legs if possible, unless you suspect a spinal injury.






